"{\"uid\": \"dailypost.ng-2024-07-29-paris-2024-olympics-super-falcons-can-beat-japan-to-qualify-waldrum\", \"text\": \"Published  on  By  Super Falcons head coach, Randy Waldrum is optimistic his side can still earn a berth in the quarter-finals at the 2024 Olympic Games.  The West Africans fell to a slim 1-0 defeat against world champions Spain in Nantes on Sunday.  It was their second defeat in Group C following last Thursday's 1-0 loss to Brazil.  The Super Falcons will need to beat Japan in their last group game on Wednesday to have any chance of making it to the last eight.  Waldrum is confident his side can beat the Asian champions.  \\\"The way the matches had gone, we still needed a result against Japan and had the chance of going through, so whether we lose or we draw, we still had the opportunity,\\\" the American explained.  \\\"I think if we beat Japan depending on what happens in Canada's group since they have got six points.\\\"  Transfer: Onyedika not ready to accept Saudi big offer  Transfer: Calafiori's shirt number at Arsenal confirmed  2026 WAFCON: 'It would not happen for other tournaments' - Super Falcons' Plumptre slams CAF  WAFCON 2026: Super Falcons Ajibade disappointed with postponement  WAFCON 2026: Super Falcons decamped after postponement  Friendly: Cameroon coach gives reason for defeat to Super Falcons  Friendly: Babajide relishes Super Falcons' win over Cameroon  Friendly: Super Falcons floor Cameroon 3-1 in Yaounde  Copyright \\u00a9Daily Post Media Ltd\"}"